If there was a conductor to fit a knight, it was Vernon Handley.
I knew him well in two decades, when he directed the Guildford Philharmonic from 1962 to 1982.
Over the past 40 years or so, I have reviewed more than 100 of his concerts and I can honestly say that I have never been disappointed by either of them – and I have been inspired many times.
